The paper deals with the problem of distributed consensus in ad hoc sensor networks, which involves the convergence of iterative algorithms based on network topology and weights. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.SY (systems and control), cs.MA (multiagent systems), cs.NI (networking and internet architecture), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), and cs.LG (machine learning). Among these, cs.SY and cs.MA are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the problem of distributed consensus and control. The other categories are also possible as they involve aspects of networking, distributed computing, and optimization, which are relevant to the paper.
